<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Setup - Miiverse Clone</title>
    <style>
      .step {
        display: none;
      }

      .step.active {
        display: block;
      }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div id="step1" class="step active">
      <h1>Welcome to Stupidverse!</h1>
      <p>
        Stupidverse is a gaming community that connects people from all over the
        world using Mii characters. Use Stupidverse to share your gaming
        experiences and meet people from around the world
      </p>
      <button>Close</button>
      <button onclick="nextStep()">Next</button>
    </div>

    <div id="step2" class="step">
      <h1>What is Stupidverse?</h1>
      <p>
        Stupidverse is a tiny clone of Miiverse that I decided to work on
        because I was bored. Eventually you'll be able to post, draw, and share
        content with others using this platform!
      </p>
      <button>Back</button>
      <button onclick="nextStep()">Next</button>
    </div>

    <div id="step3" class="step">
      <h1>Stupidverse Manners</h1>
      <hr />
      <p>
        I'm honestly too lazy to write this right now but like if you do bad
        stuff you're probally gonna get banned so like don't I guess!
      </p>
      <button>Read Stupidverse Code of Conduct</button>
      <p>Do you agree to abide by the Stupidverse Code of Conduct?</p>
      <button>I Do Not Agree</button>
      <button onclick="nextStep()">I Agree</button>
    </div>

    <div id="step4" class="step">
      <h2>Create Your Account</h2>
      <form id="setupForm" action="/setup" method="POST">
        <label for="username">Username:</label>
        <input type="text" id="username" name="username" required /><br />

        <label for="password">Password:</label>
        <input type="password" id="password" name="password" required /><br />

        <label for="gameLevel">Game Level:</label>
        <select id="gameLevel" name="gameLevel" required>
          <option value="beginner">Beginner</option>
          <option value="intermediate">Intermediate</option>
          <option value="expert">Expert</option></select
        ><br />

        <button type="submit">Create Account</button>
      </form>
    </div>

    <div id="step5" class="step">
      <h1>Ready to Start Using Stupidverse</h1>
      <hr />
      <p>
        First, check out some communities and see what people from all over the
        world are posting about. Take this opportunity to familiarize yourself
        with Stupidverse. You might make some new discoveries along the way!
      </p>
      <button onclick="nextStep()">Next</button>
    </div>

    <div id="step6" class="step">
      <h1>Have fun in Stupidverse!</h1>
      <hr />
      <button href="/communities">Start</button>
    </div>

    <script>
      let currentStep = 1;

      function nextStep() {
        document
          .getElementById(`step${currentStep}`)
          .classList.remove("active");
        currentStep++;
        document.getElementById(`step${currentStep}`).classList.add("active");
      }
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
